# GitHub Workflow Configuration for E2E Testing
# This file documents the environment variables and configuration needed for E2E testing

# Environment Variables for E2E Testing:
# - STUDIO_BASE_URL: URL where the Studio is hosted (default: http://localhost:5173)
# - API_BASE_URL: URL where the API is hosted (default: http://localhost:3000)
# - DATABASE_URL: PostgreSQL connection string for the API
# - JWT_SECRET: Secret for JWT token generation
# - NODE_ENV: Environment (test/development)

# GitHub Secrets that can be configured:
# - GITHUB_TOKEN: For accessing other repositories (like aurenworks-api)
# - API_REPOSITORY: Repository name for the API (default: aurenworks-api)
# - API_BRANCH: Branch to use for API (default: main)

# Workflow Triggers:
# - Push to main/develop branches
# - Pull requests to main/develop branches
# - Manual workflow dispatch
# - Scheduled runs (optional)

# Artifacts:
# - playwright-report/: Test results and HTML report
# - test-results/: Screenshots and videos (on failure)
# - playwright-videos/: Video recordings of test runs

# Timeout Configuration:
# - Simple workflow: 20 minutes (recommended)
# - CI workflow: 30 minutes for E2E tests

# Services:
# - Mock API server (primary - uses mock-api-server.cjs)
# - PostgreSQL 15 with health checks (optional, for real API)
# - Real API server (optional, if available)

# Browser Support:
# - Chromium (default)
# - Can be extended to Firefox and WebKit if needed

# Test Data:
# - Uses seed.sh script for test data
# - Fallback to mock data if seeding fails
# - Supports both real and mock API scenarios
